The article discusses the recipients of the Nobel Peace Prize for this year, including Ales Bialiatski of Belarus, Ukraine's Center for Civil Liberties, and the Russian organization Memorial. These individuals and organizations have been recognized for their tireless efforts in fighting for human rights and fundamental freedoms, such as the right to speak freely and criticize openly. Despite facing intimidation and oppression, they have remained steadfast in their pursuit of justice and have exposed the truth about political repression and abuse. The article emphasizes the importance of their work in strengthening our world and inspiring hope for a better future.